President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed May 20 through May 26, 2023, as National Safe Boating Week in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of safe boating practices and encourages Americans to learn more about boating safety and take advantage of boating safety education opportunities. It highlights the need for planning ahead, ensuring vessels meet safety standards, and obtaining free boat inspections from the civilian Coast Guard Auxiliary. The proclamation also emphasizes the significance of simple safety measures such as wearing life jackets, checking weather forecasts, using maps in unfamiliar areas, and avoiding alcohol or drugs while operating boats. The President acknowledges the dedication of the United States Coast Guard and other government partners who work to protect boaters and rescue those in need. The proclamation urges governors and officials at all levels of government to promote boating safety in their communities.